      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.13770v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        We consider a class of Hamiltonians describing a fermion field coupled to a boson field. The interaction kernels are assumed bounded in the fermionic momentum variable and decaying like $|q|^{-p}$ for large boson momenta $q$. A realistic physical case would be $p=\frac12$. We impose a spatial cutoff and UV-renormalise the resulting Hamiltonian by subtracting its ground state energy. Our renormalis&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.13770v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.13770v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
