        An integrable Hamiltonian system presents monodromy if the action-angle variables cannot be defined globally. We consider a classical system with azimuthal symmetry and explore the topology structure of its phase space. Based on the behavior of closed orbits around singular points or regions of the energy-momentum plane, a semi-theoretical method is derived to detect classical monodromy. The valid&hellip;
        <a class="is-size-7" style="white-space: nowrap;" onclick="document.getElementById('2103.13711v1-abstract-full').style.display = 'inline'; document.getElementById('2103.13711v1-abstract-short').style.display = 'none';">&#9661; More</a>
