      <span class="abstract-short has-text-grey-dark mathjax" id="2103.13277v1-abstract-short" style="display: inline;">
        A weak topological insulator in dimension $3$ is known to have a topologically protected gapless mode along the screw dislocation. In this paper we formulate and prove this fact with the language of C*-algebra K-theory. The proof is based on the coarse index theory of the helical surface.
        
